<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                                <head>No. 33.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Carter</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blount</persName>.</hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Honolulu, Hawaiian Islands</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6, 1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Regarding elections held in this
                                    Kingdom prior to 1887 as to the proportion of foreign residents
                                    other than Asiatics, who were qualified voters for
                                    representatives, I may say that I had a personal interest in two
                                    elections prior to 1880, one in Honolulu, island of Oahu, and
                                    one in Wailuka, island of Maui, and was also a candidate for
                                    Honolulu, on two occasions between 1880 and 1887; that I was
                                    familiar with the lists of voters, and can safely say that less
                                    than 30 per cent of the foreign residents were naturalized.</p>
                                <p>Very respectfully, yours,</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. O.
                                    Carter.</hi></signed></closer>
                                <postscript>
                                    <p>His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">James H.
                                            Blount</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">U. S. Minister
                                            Resident, etc.</hi></p>
                                </postscript>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>